# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CODEOWNERS — merge-time guardrail for Vocaband's critical flows.
#
# A pull request that touches any path below cannot be merged until the listed
# owner approves it — BUT only once "Require review from Code Owners" is turned
# on in the branch-protection rule for `main`. Until that switch is flipped in
# GitHub settings, this file only AUTO-REQUESTS the owner's review; it does not
# block merges. See docs/operator-tasks.md for the one-time setup checklist.
#
# This is intentionally NOT a global `*` rule: only the auth / AI / backend /
# database / config paths that silently break the whole app are gated.
# Everything else merges under the normal review flow, so day-to-day work
# (UI tweaks, copy, new game content) is never slowed down.
#
# The owner handle below assumes the repo owner is @ward3107 — change it if you
# use a different GitHub username or want a team (e.g. @your-org/maintainers).
# An invalid handle silently disables enforcement, so double-check it matches.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

